commit.message:
Fix off-by-1 max file name len in dfp/dfr8 (#706)

The "last file name" arrays in both dfp.c and dfr8.c can only
hold DF_MAXFNLEN - 1 characters, so a file name of of length
DF_MAXFNLEN (defined in hlimits.h) would be truncated.

This has little practical effect, as it's just used in a shortcut
used when reopening files, but it's incorrect behavior and raises
warnings. Other "last file" shortcut code uses correctly-sized
arrays.

verification.payload:
tree 23f38adfc9262696fe693c2ceaec1d2435ce6bcd
parent 6cb7dc316d680bec15659228fcd97f01ee6bf4de
author Dana Robinson <43805+derobins@users.noreply.github.com> 1711695537 -0700
committer GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1711695537 -0700

commit.message:
Fix memory leaks (#702)

The list of cdf structures were not properly de-allocated, causing memory
leaks.  However, releasing the memory caused a number segfaults in several
tests.

Re-worked the code that increases the size of the cdf list when application
attempts to open more files than the current max number of files that can
be opened at the same time.  This allowed the library to properly release
the allocated memory and eliminated the memory leaks.  Verified with valgrind.

verification.payload:
tree 47c7d3cb99c97b0c1f61b32f1e1e3a980c0f08a1
parent 32ddd7ca667bcfeeacead59caa6f2f975110698f
author bmribler <39579120+bmribler@users.noreply.github.com> 1711637112 -0400
committer GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1711637112 -0700

Fix memory leaks (#702)

The list of cdf structures were not properly de-allocated, causing memory

commit.message:
Change how library tests run (#693)

The Autotools ran the mfhdf tests via a script, which is unnecessary.
They now run directly.

CMake ran hdf and mfhdf tests using PASS_REGULAR_EXPRESSION, which
has proved to be flaky, when CTest can't find the regular
expression. These tests are now run directly and the exit code
inspected.
